1
00:02:02,966 --> 00:02:04,986
Thank you, Mom.

2
00:02:04,986 --> 00:02:06,495
Thank you to those in the back as well.

3
00:02:06,495 --> 00:02:07,400
Thank you.

4
00:02:09,500 --> 00:02:10,666
See you again tomorrow.

5
00:02:26,700 --> 00:02:28,933
Yes, thank you very much.

6
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:54,845
Thank you.

7
00:02:55,984 --> 00:03:01,914
Thank you.

8
00:03:26,600 --> 00:03:29,000
This is the costume that helps us earn our living.

9
00:03:30,666 --> 00:03:33,133
We must help each other take good care of it, my child.

10
00:03:34,133 --> 00:03:34,933
Yes, Father.

11
00:03:39,266 --> 00:03:40,890
His dancing has improved a lot.

12
00:03:40,890 --> 00:03:41,390
Right.

13
00:03:42,666 --> 00:03:45,200
Phet, do you know what Likay actually is?

14
00:03:47,133 --> 00:03:49,232
Others might look at it...

15
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:51,866
As just local folk art.

16
00:03:52,559 --> 00:03:54,906
A performance that is outdated.

17
00:03:55,748 --> 00:03:57,455
But if everyone thinks like that,

18
00:03:59,485 --> 00:04:00,539
One day,

19
00:04:00,787 --> 00:04:02,359
Likay will gradually disappear.

20
00:04:04,934 --> 00:04:06,271
As those who possess

21
00:04:06,271 --> 00:04:09,000
the knowledge to carry on the Likay culture,

22
00:04:10,866 --> 00:04:11,637
Son,

23
00:04:12,726 --> 00:04:14,616
I entrust the Petchprakai Likay Troupe to you.

24
00:04:16,466 --> 00:04:18,666
It might not be something of great monetary value,

25
00:04:20,066 --> 00:04:21,933
But it is a national treasure.

26
00:04:22,666 --> 00:04:25,733
And it is also the lifeblood of many people, my son.

27
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:28,732
Phet,

28
00:04:29,722 --> 00:04:31,648
The future of the Likay...

29
00:04:33,183 --> 00:04:34,748
Is in your hands now.

30
00:04:39,333 --> 00:04:40,852
I will take good care of it.

31
00:04:43,031 --> 00:04:43,910
Both my sister,

32
00:04:45,989 --> 00:04:46,817
The Likay art,

33
00:04:48,500 --> 00:04:50,333
And our Petchprakai Troupe.

34
00:04:52,400 --> 00:04:54,021
I’ll be waiting to see the day Phet...

35
00:04:54,417 --> 00:04:56,962
Leads this troupe to national fame.

36
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:02,266
I’m counting on you, son.

37
00:05:54,566 --> 00:05:56,211
♪ Your child is in… ♪

38
00:05:57,349 --> 00:05:59,349
♪ Deep mourning… ♪

39
00:06:00,488 --> 00:06:04,181
♪ With a breaking heart… ♪

40
00:06:04,933 --> 00:06:06,948
As those who possess the knowledge
(Phet Thae) ♪ Thinking of ♪

41
00:06:06,948 --> 00:06:09,676
to carry on the Likay performance, son…
(Phet Thae) ♪ the stories… ♪

42
00:06:10,666 --> 00:06:13,700
I entrust the Petchprakai Troupe to you...
(Phet Thae) ♪ Behind the scenes ♪

43
00:06:14,740 --> 00:06:16,479
♪ Father has departed. ♪

44
00:06:17,271 --> 00:06:21,078
♪ Your child is powerless.♪

45
00:06:22,563 --> 00:06:25,641
♪ Father was the example...♪

46
00:06:26,866 --> 00:06:28,112
♪ Of greatness.♪

47
00:06:28,800 --> 00:06:29,966
Thank you everyone very much...

48
00:06:31,300 --> 00:06:32,907
♪ Every word ♪
For joining us to send off

49
00:06:32,907 --> 00:06:34,533
♪ Father entreated...♪
Father Thongplaeo for the last time.

50
00:06:36,066 --> 00:06:37,846
♪ Taught and instructed...♪

51
00:06:38,133 --> 00:06:39,000
I, Phet Thae,

52
00:06:39,966 --> 00:06:41,410
♪ Every...♪

53
00:06:41,966 --> 00:06:44,900
♪ matter.♪
Promise to carry on Father’s intentions...

54
00:06:46,166 --> 00:06:47,473
♪ Don't be… ♪

55
00:06:48,067 --> 00:06:49,654
♪ Envious...♪

56
00:06:50,248 --> 00:06:52,061
♪ Of anyone...♪

57
00:06:52,533 --> 00:06:54,754
And will take care of the Petchprakai Troupe...

58
00:06:55,002 --> 00:06:56,388
♪ This is… ♪

59
00:06:56,388 --> 00:06:57,488
That Father loved...

60
00:06:57,488 --> 00:06:59,333
The best I can.

61
00:07:00,917 --> 00:07:03,645
♪ Father used...♪

62
00:07:06,752 --> 00:07:08,112
♪ I will...♪

63
00:07:08,360 --> 00:07:09,662
♪ Dedicate myself...♪

64
00:07:11,791 --> 00:07:15,010
♪ According to your words...♪

65
00:07:17,387 --> 00:07:18,575
♪ With...♪

66
00:07:19,070 --> 00:07:20,953
♪ Love.♪

67
00:07:21,894 --> 00:07:24,146
♪ Farewell...♪

68
00:07:26,077 --> 00:07:29,874
♪ In mourning.♪

69
00:08:17,266 --> 00:08:18,106
P’Phet, do you know?

70
00:08:19,690 --> 00:08:20,834
Even though Father is no longer here,

71
00:08:22,270 --> 00:08:23,117
But Guy feels...

72
00:08:25,098 --> 00:08:26,545
Father is still watching over us.

73
00:08:28,179 --> 00:08:29,394
From somewhere out there.

74
00:08:31,820 --> 00:08:32,600
Right.

75
00:08:34,266 --> 00:08:35,966
Anyway, don't give up yet.

76
00:08:37,066 --> 00:08:38,300
Let’s fight through this together.

77
00:08:39,800 --> 00:08:41,400
Anything I can help with,

78
00:08:42,866 --> 00:08:44,400
I will help you to my fullest.

79
00:08:47,500 --> 00:08:48,209
Help...

80
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:52,023
Help get me some water, the smoke got in my eyes.

81
00:09:02,566 --> 00:09:03,500
Totally ruined the mood!

82
00:09:04,400 --> 00:09:05,866
And here I was comforting you for so long.

83
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:07,800
Seriously!

84
00:09:08,100 --> 00:09:09,566
People were actually worried.

85
00:09:10,700 --> 00:09:11,666
And you're just joking around.

86
00:09:15,500 --> 00:09:17,420
But honestly, it is quite sad.

87
00:09:20,638 --> 00:09:22,090
But I don't know why we should stay sad.

88
00:09:23,575 --> 00:09:24,075
Because...

89
00:09:24,768 --> 00:09:26,462
I believe Father would want to see you...

90
00:09:27,353 --> 00:09:28,666
Rise up as a leader,

91
00:09:29,607 --> 00:09:30,984
As the head of the Petchprakai Troupe instead.

92
00:09:39,866 --> 00:09:40,880
True.

93
00:09:42,068 --> 00:09:42,580
Then,

94
00:09:44,512 --> 00:09:46,240
Let’s help each other take Petchprakai far...

95
00:09:47,626 --> 00:09:48,967
Until we get a World Tour!

96
00:09:51,600 --> 00:09:52,575
That’s excessive!

97
00:09:52,922 --> 00:09:54,417
Or an Asia Tour would be fine too.

98
00:09:55,160 --> 00:09:56,154
Guy wants to fly on a plane.

99
00:09:56,996 --> 00:09:58,085
Guy wants to know...

100
00:09:58,431 --> 00:09:59,557
If in the sky,

101
00:10:00,448 --> 00:10:02,016
Mekhala the Goddess really exists.

102
00:10:03,333 --> 00:10:04,133
Oh!

103
00:10:04,333 --> 00:10:05,133
Just the thought...

104
00:10:05,700 --> 00:10:06,966
Is already amazing.

105
00:10:07,200 --> 00:10:10,066
Guy wants the window seat!

106
00:10:10,800 --> 00:10:12,166
I’ll book the window seat,

107
00:10:12,366 --> 00:10:13,733
And then you two can sit together.

108
00:10:13,800 --> 00:10:14,600
Okay?

109
00:10:14,933 --> 00:10:15,933
Let’s just get there first.

110
00:10:16,533 --> 00:10:17,333
P’Phet.

111
00:10:19,133 --> 00:10:21,133
Go to the front of the house, someone is here.

112
00:10:21,966 --> 00:10:22,830
Who is it?

113
00:10:23,721 --> 00:10:25,350
The troupe is on a break during this time, aren't we?

114
00:10:26,666 --> 00:10:27,531
But this person...

115
00:10:28,917 --> 00:10:30,000
Just go take a look.

116
00:10:38,466 --> 00:10:40,266
If one comes, we call him Ping.

117
00:10:41,066 --> 00:10:41,866
If two come,

118
00:10:42,166 --> 00:10:42,966
Ping Pong.

119
00:10:43,333 --> 00:10:45,300
If three come, we call them Ping Pong Chae.

120
00:10:45,500 --> 00:10:46,500
Ah, Ping Pong Chae.

121
00:10:46,733 --> 00:10:47,566
Ah, Ping Pong Chae.

122
00:10:47,933 --> 00:10:48,733
Ah, Ping Pong Chae.

123
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:49,800
Ah, Ping Pong Chae.

124
00:10:50,166 --> 00:10:50,933
Ping Pong Chae.

125
00:10:50,933 --> 00:10:51,766
Ah, Ping Pong Chae.

126
00:10:52,200 --> 00:10:53,000
Ping Pong Chae.

127
00:10:53,400 --> 00:10:54,666
Ping Pong Chae.

128
00:10:55,100 --> 00:10:56,600
Ping Pong Chae.

129
00:10:59,566 --> 00:11:00,800
I'll take the conversation from here.

130
00:11:12,400 --> 00:11:13,400
Hello, Mr. Ar.

131
00:11:15,533 --> 00:11:16,333
Who is it?

132
00:11:16,733 --> 00:11:18,566
Hello, Nephew Phet.

133
00:11:19,866 --> 00:11:20,891
How is it going?

134
00:11:21,337 --> 00:11:24,746
Since Master Thongplaeo passed away...

135
00:11:25,300 --> 00:11:26,200
How is the troupe doing?

136
00:11:27,066 --> 00:11:30,133
We're taking a break to get settled for a moment.

137
00:11:31,300 --> 00:11:32,260
And...

138
00:11:33,696 --> 00:11:36,733
Do you have some business here, Mr. Ar?

139
00:11:37,100 --> 00:11:39,400
Hmm, definitely.

140
00:11:43,866 --> 00:11:45,214
I'm here to collect the money...

141
00:11:46,204 --> 00:11:48,232
That Master Thongplaeo owed.

142
00:11:57,533 --> 00:11:58,333
Uh...

143
00:11:59,800 --> 00:12:01,966
How much is it?

144
00:12:02,666 --> 00:12:03,466
Five million.

145
00:12:03,900 --> 00:12:04,700
Five million?

146
00:12:05,933 --> 00:12:06,733
Correct.

147
00:12:07,266 --> 00:12:08,066
Five million.

148
00:12:10,366 --> 00:12:12,337
If Nephew Phet doesn't believe me,

149
00:12:12,337 --> 00:12:14,054
There is a contract...

150
00:12:14,500 --> 00:12:16,877
That Father Thongplaeo made.

151
00:12:17,224 --> 00:12:18,199
Kumphet.

152
00:12:30,066 --> 00:12:31,900
This contract was made...

153
00:12:32,533 --> 00:12:34,700
The payment was due since last year.

154
00:12:35,366 --> 00:12:39,000
Father Thongplaeo already paid five hundred thousand.

155
00:12:41,066 --> 00:12:44,100
So there's four million five hundred thousand remaining.

156
00:12:45,500 --> 00:12:46,370
Let’s just say

157
00:12:47,063 --> 00:12:50,376
we should talk about the numbers

158
00:12:50,376 --> 00:12:52,466
that are still quite lingering.

159
00:12:53,266 --> 00:12:54,066
Shall we?

160
00:12:56,166 --> 00:12:57,966
Cold water, refreshing, is here!

161
00:13:22,300 --> 00:13:23,744
Very sweet!

162
00:13:23,992 --> 00:13:24,641
Thank you.

163
00:13:24,987 --> 00:13:25,898
You're welcome.

164
00:13:26,467 --> 00:13:27,364
I'll excuse myself now.

165
00:13:27,364 --> 00:13:28,027
Mm-hmm.

166
00:13:30,206 --> 00:13:31,542
Why didn't you bring a whole jar?

167
00:13:32,582 --> 00:13:33,940
One glass isn't enough.

168
00:13:35,524 --> 00:13:36,716
I...

169
00:13:37,800 --> 00:13:40,700
Would like to request to pay in installments, Mr. Ar.

170
00:13:41,500 --> 00:13:42,300
Installments?

171
00:13:44,400 --> 00:13:45,200
Yes.

172
00:13:49,200 --> 00:13:50,666
Fine, fine.

173
00:13:51,700 --> 00:13:52,207
And...

174
00:13:53,247 --> 00:13:56,014
How does Nephew Phet want to split the payments?

175
00:13:57,333 --> 00:13:58,133
Well...

176
00:13:58,900 --> 00:14:01,566
Hey, what is Mr. Ar saying?

177
00:14:03,200 --> 00:14:04,000
I don't know.

178
00:14:04,466 --> 00:14:05,766
I'm reading his lips right now.

179
00:14:06,400 --> 00:14:07,566
"""Five"" something, I don't know."

180
00:14:07,933 --> 00:14:09,400
Mr. Ar said...

181
00:14:12,266 --> 00:14:13,066
Oh!

182
00:14:14,400 --> 00:14:15,200
Nonsense.

183
00:14:17,400 --> 00:14:18,900
What are they talking about, P’Ploy?

184
00:14:19,733 --> 00:14:21,366
Hmm, I don't know either.

185
00:14:22,366 --> 00:14:23,248
But...

186
00:14:23,496 --> 00:14:24,980
I saw a contract.

187
00:14:25,525 --> 00:14:26,848
A loan agreement.

188
00:14:27,333 --> 00:14:28,133
Huh?

189
00:14:29,666 --> 00:14:30,800
A loan agreement?

190
00:14:31,366 --> 00:14:32,666
Monthly...

191
00:14:34,300 --> 00:14:37,766
At fifty thousand baht per installment...

192
00:14:38,400 --> 00:14:39,510
Ninety installments.

193
00:14:40,302 --> 00:14:41,568
Ninety installments.

194
00:14:41,816 --> 00:14:43,115
Seven years...

195
00:14:43,115 --> 00:14:44,099
And five months.

196
00:14:44,743 --> 00:14:45,414
Nephew Phet,

197
00:14:45,860 --> 00:14:47,465
That’s too long, Nephew.

198
00:14:49,400 --> 00:14:50,733
But I understand.

199
00:14:51,966 --> 00:14:53,866
You just lost Master Thongplaeo.

200
00:14:54,333 --> 00:14:54,895
The troupe...

201
00:14:55,489 --> 00:14:57,166
Has to start over.

202
00:14:57,166 --> 00:14:57,966
Right?

203
00:15:00,966 --> 00:15:02,100
Let’s do this.

204
00:15:03,200 --> 00:15:04,257
I...

205
00:15:04,554 --> 00:15:06,797
Am not a heartless person.

206
00:15:07,066 --> 00:15:07,734
Let’s say...

207
00:15:09,120 --> 00:15:10,432
We should meet…

208
00:15:11,422 --> 00:15:12,139
halfway.

209
00:15:13,377 --> 00:15:13,877
One hundred thousand.

210
00:15:16,309 --> 00:15:16,933
Can you do that?

211
00:15:19,133 --> 00:15:20,146
Fine.

212
00:15:21,037 --> 00:15:21,814
Kam-Phet,

213
00:15:22,557 --> 00:15:23,933
A new contract, now

214
00:15:29,933 --> 00:15:36,100
Think about it, or you can take it to think first.

215
00:15:38,566 --> 00:15:39,703
But during this time,

216
00:15:40,198 --> 00:15:41,982
While you are thinking,

217
00:15:43,533 --> 00:15:45,566
I'll take the interest first.

218
00:15:46,366 --> 00:15:47,166
This time.

219
00:15:47,700 --> 00:15:48,500
Okay?

220
00:15:49,600 --> 00:15:50,400
Kam-Phet,

221
00:15:51,066 --> 00:15:51,866
Kam-ploy,

222
00:15:53,000 --> 00:15:54,053
Go get the interest.

223
00:16:12,200 --> 00:16:14,066
Don't be startled.

224
00:16:19,933 --> 00:16:21,966
Once I get the first installment,

225
00:16:23,666 --> 00:16:24,800
I will return it.

226
00:16:25,466 --> 00:16:26,266
Okay?

227
00:16:27,900 --> 00:16:30,133
And Nephew Phet,

228
00:16:31,866 --> 00:16:33,133
Don't forget to call me.

229
00:16:41,005 --> 00:16:42,016
Kam-phet, Kam-ploy,

230
00:16:42,016 --> 00:16:42,743
Let's go.

231
00:17:00,933 --> 00:17:01,733
A hundred thousand a month...

232
00:17:02,400 --> 00:17:03,818
Will we be able to afford it, P’Phet?

233
00:17:04,040 --> 00:17:04,666
Guy...

234
00:17:08,766 --> 00:17:09,966
We have to make it happen.

235
00:17:12,200 --> 00:17:12,700
Because...

236
00:17:14,760 --> 00:17:15,920
Father took out the loan...

237
00:17:16,266 --> 00:17:18,866
To develop our Likay troupe.

238
00:17:20,133 --> 00:17:22,066
And if we can't pay back this debt,

239
00:17:22,666 --> 00:17:24,566
It means our troupe won't develop.

240
00:17:26,500 --> 00:17:28,466
Which I definitely won't let happen.

241
00:17:30,766 --> 00:17:31,566
That’s true.

242
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:35,412
Then let’s make the Petchprakai Troupe famous...

243
00:17:35,880 --> 00:17:37,466
Until we get to play at Rajamangala Stadium!

244
00:17:37,866 --> 00:17:38,666
Is that good?

245
00:17:38,666 --> 00:17:39,366
Good, good!

246
00:17:39,366 --> 00:17:40,166
Good, right?

247
00:17:40,666 --> 00:17:42,360
And have a world tour too.

248
00:17:42,360 --> 00:17:43,600
Yeah!

249
00:17:44,166 --> 00:17:46,933
If that’s the case, then we can go dance with Nong Noey.

250
00:17:47,166 --> 00:17:47,673
Hey!

251
00:17:47,673 --> 00:17:51,653
Nong Noey, Nong Noey!

252
00:17:53,785 --> 00:17:54,579
It's okay.

253
00:17:56,240 --> 00:17:56,960
We can do it.

254
00:18:00,000 --> 00:18:01,603
I and P’Jom Thian...

255
00:18:02,080 --> 00:18:03,881
Would like to leave the troupe first.

256
00:18:04,480 --> 00:18:06,080
Now that there's no Master anymore,

257
00:18:07,015 --> 00:18:08,200
I feel it's just not right.

258
00:18:08,733 --> 00:18:10,733
And why didn't you tell P’Phet yourself?

259
00:18:10,933 --> 00:18:11,638
In that case,

260
00:18:12,600 --> 00:18:13,300
I’ll take my leave.

261
00:18:19,700 --> 00:18:20,791
P’Phet...

262
00:18:21,160 --> 00:18:23,000
I and the team... are here to resign.

263
00:18:23,400 --> 00:18:25,142
Is there something wrong? If...

264
00:18:25,984 --> 00:18:27,933
There’s a problem anywhere, you can tell me.

265
00:18:28,366 --> 00:18:31,100
Since there's no Master, we have no passion at all.

266
00:18:33,300 --> 00:18:34,100
Thank you very much.

267
00:18:41,440 --> 00:18:41,960
Oh, hey!

268
00:18:42,520 --> 00:18:43,425
Come help move these things quickly!

269
00:18:48,200 --> 00:18:50,570
I'm going to join another troupe first.

270
00:18:50,760 --> 00:18:52,134
They've been inviting me for a long time.

271
00:18:52,920 --> 00:18:53,866
I’m leaving now.

272
00:18:57,766 --> 00:18:58,672
P’Phet...

273
00:18:58,880 --> 00:18:59,900
More people are leaving?

274
00:19:01,866 --> 00:19:03,100
Everyone is leaving.

275
00:19:11,198 --> 00:19:12,944
I would like to announce right here...

276
00:19:12,944 --> 00:19:14,267
That I and Chan Dao...

277
00:19:14,800 --> 00:19:15,962
Now, the two of us...

278
00:19:16,457 --> 00:19:18,749
Have left the Petchprakai Likay Troupe.

279
00:19:21,471 --> 00:19:22,827
I knew it.

280
00:19:23,565 --> 00:19:25,244
Why did you leave?

281
00:19:25,690 --> 00:19:26,532
Both of you?

282
00:19:27,333 --> 00:19:28,006
Yes.

283
00:19:28,006 --> 00:19:30,418
We left together because...

284
00:19:30,418 --> 00:19:32,066
We want to find new experiences.

285
00:19:32,900 --> 00:19:35,923
And we've been with Petchprakai for almost twenty years.

286
00:19:35,923 --> 00:19:37,063
So you feel fulfilled,

287
00:19:37,063 --> 00:19:37,933
right?

288
00:19:38,933 --> 00:19:39,498
Yes.

289
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:40,907
Now,

290
00:19:41,600 --> 00:19:43,670
Any host who wants the two of us...

291
00:19:44,116 --> 00:19:45,208
To perform at your event,

292
00:19:45,604 --> 00:19:46,974
Please contact us.

293
00:19:47,321 --> 00:19:48,297
Or...

294
00:19:48,644 --> 00:19:50,683
If any Likay troupe wants us

295
00:19:50,683 --> 00:19:51,961
to join the performance,

296
00:19:52,308 --> 00:19:53,454
You can message us.

297
00:19:53,850 --> 00:19:55,573
Right now, the two of us are ready.

298
00:19:56,248 --> 00:19:57,121
My son is about to be ordained, I’ll message you.

299
00:19:57,121 --> 00:19:58,166
Start your own troupe! #FCJomThian

300
00:19:58,166 --> 00:20:00,000
Good for you. Your talent can go further than this.

301
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:02,526
Petchprakai without the Master isn't worth staying.

302
00:20:02,526 --> 00:20:05,319
End of Father Thongplaeo’s era = End of Petchprakai’s era.

303
00:20:14,700 --> 00:20:15,640
P’Phet...

304
00:20:16,185 --> 00:20:17,366
Don't look at it.

305
00:20:19,800 --> 00:20:21,039
It's okay.

306
00:20:21,930 --> 00:20:23,472
Once the main captain is missing,

307
00:20:24,165 --> 00:20:26,196
Everyone is naturally worried.

308
00:20:27,333 --> 00:20:30,533
Should I use a burner account to bash those trolls?

309
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:32,271
No need, Ploy.

310
00:20:33,113 --> 00:20:34,248
I'm really okay.

311
00:20:36,866 --> 00:20:37,666
Fine.

312
00:20:39,800 --> 00:20:40,823
And what about you, Ploy?

313
00:20:42,011 --> 00:20:43,415
Have you thought about leaving the troupe?

314
00:20:46,266 --> 00:20:47,866
Why do you ask like that?

315
00:20:49,900 --> 00:20:50,400
Well...

316
00:20:51,093 --> 00:20:52,565
If you want to leave, you can.

317
00:20:52,862 --> 00:20:53,856
I won't stop you.

318
00:20:55,094 --> 00:20:58,114
Because either way, Father isn't here anymore.

319
00:20:59,766 --> 00:21:01,357
So what if Father isn't here?

320
00:21:02,446 --> 00:21:03,888
Everyone else is still here, right?

321
00:21:05,225 --> 00:21:06,244
P’Phet...

322
00:21:06,838 --> 00:21:08,147
If you still need me,

323
00:21:08,791 --> 00:21:10,241
I... will stay by your side.

324
00:21:11,231 --> 00:21:14,481
But if the day comes when you don't need me anymore...

325
00:21:15,224 --> 00:21:16,813
I will...

326
00:21:20,594 --> 00:21:21,503
I...

327
00:21:22,642 --> 00:21:23,497
Won't go anywhere.

328
00:21:23,893 --> 00:21:28,391
Because the food here is delicious and it's free too!

329
00:21:30,200 --> 00:21:31,128
You silly kid.

330
00:21:31,821 --> 00:21:34,831
Let’s go eat. The others have probably been waiting a long time.

331
00:21:34,831 --> 00:21:37,066
Today we have onion flowers and stir-fried liver.

332
00:21:37,700 --> 00:21:39,100
Your favorite too.

333
00:21:40,400 --> 00:21:41,200
Really?

334
00:21:43,766 --> 00:21:45,843
Yeah, it’s mine too

335
00:21:45,843 --> 00:21:48,128
just go eat, I’m hungry,

336
00:21:48,128 --> 00:21:49,472
my stomach is growling!

337
00:21:49,472 --> 00:21:50,366
Yay!

338
00:21:50,866 --> 00:21:53,346
Alright everyone,

339
00:22:00,000 --> 00:22:01,386
Ugh, I’m so hungry,

340
00:22:01,386 --> 00:22:02,431
Right now I want to eat…

341
00:22:02,925 --> 00:22:03,440
Massaman curry.

342
00:22:03,440 --> 00:22:04,004
Chicken curry.

343
00:22:04,004 --> 00:22:04,504
Lemongrass salad.

344
00:22:04,504 --> 00:22:05,004
Spicy stir-fry.

345
00:22:05,504 --> 00:22:06,351
Okay, okay!

346
00:22:06,351 --> 00:22:07,268
That’s enough!

347
00:22:07,768 --> 00:22:08,268
Stir-fried stink beans with chili.

348
00:22:08,268 --> 00:22:09,226
Stir-fried squid with shrimp paste.

349
00:22:09,226 --> 00:22:10,221
You wanna eat?

350
00:22:10,518 --> 00:22:11,339
Yes, I do!

351
00:22:13,121 --> 00:22:13,935
Hey, Pleng!

352
00:22:15,530 --> 00:22:16,977
Eat first.

353
00:22:17,918 --> 00:22:19,411
Then play games.

354
00:22:20,700 --> 00:22:21,649
Alright, everyone.

355
00:22:21,996 --> 00:22:22,830
Before we eat today,

356
00:22:22,830 --> 00:22:24,528
I have something I want to say to you all.

357
00:22:24,924 --> 00:22:26,616
I want to thank everyone very much...

358
00:22:27,062 --> 00:22:29,511
For still staying with the Petchprakai Likay Troupe.

359
00:22:30,254 --> 00:22:32,148
Even though Father is no longer here.

360
00:22:33,666 --> 00:22:34,410
And...

361
00:22:35,598 --> 00:22:37,802
I, as the new troupe leader,

362
00:22:39,436 --> 00:22:40,001
I…

363
00:22:40,001 --> 00:22:43,034
I've decided that I will focus on
taking care of the troupe fully.

364
00:22:43,381 --> 00:22:44,652
And I won't perform anymore.

365
00:22:53,600 --> 00:22:54,267
Because

366
00:22:54,267 --> 00:22:56,600
I will train a new Likay lead.

367
00:22:56,848 --> 00:22:57,645
Hah!

368
00:23:07,966 --> 00:23:08,900
Tho Pra-kai

369
00:23:09,247 --> 00:23:11,880
is the new lead actor of our troupe.

370
00:23:11,880 --> 00:23:13,420
Yay!

371
00:23:16,666 --> 00:23:19,566
I will train Guy to be
a nationally famous Likay lead.

372
00:23:20,000 --> 00:23:23,133
As for the world tour we talked about,
I will make it come true.

373
00:23:28,211 --> 00:23:29,477
Yay!

374
00:23:31,146 --> 00:23:32,815
The new likay lead actor.

375
00:23:34,102 --> 00:23:35,691
Can I get your autograph?

376
00:23:35,691 --> 00:23:37,033
Can I take a photo with you?

377
00:23:37,033 --> 00:23:38,766
Can I get your autograph?

378
00:23:38,766 --> 00:23:40,913
Bring the spoons and forks, let’s eat!

379
00:23:46,666 --> 00:23:47,837
Eat, eat!

380
00:23:51,748 --> 00:23:53,579
For Guy
(Pleng Chai) Water! Water! Water!

381
00:23:53,579 --> 00:23:54,726
Would you like anything, sir?

382
00:24:24,866 --> 00:24:26,896
The food looks so good

383
00:24:26,896 --> 00:24:28,498
enjoy your meal.

384
00:24:29,340 --> 00:24:31,387
Eat, eat!

385
00:24:52,566 --> 00:24:55,023
Serve yourself first.

386
00:24:56,500 --> 00:24:57,566
He’s been waiting a long time.

387
00:24:57,966 --> 00:24:59,133
Wait for me, the lead actor, first!

388
00:24:59,500 --> 00:25:00,733
Lead actor, lead actor!

389
00:25:00,966 --> 00:25:04,300
Ooh, the lead actor has to eat a lot
to be big and strong.

390
00:25:33,933 --> 00:25:35,108
Tho Pra-kai...

391
00:25:35,900 --> 00:25:38,692
Is the new lead actor of our troupe.

392
00:25:52,466 --> 00:25:54,133
Oh, shit, it's ten o'clock.

393
00:25:58,500 --> 00:26:00,644
I hope that from now on,

394
00:26:00,892 --> 00:26:03,014
Only good things come into my life.

395
00:26:47,900 --> 00:26:48,700
Guy!

396
00:26:50,100 --> 00:26:51,766
Why are you sweating like this?

397
00:26:52,466 --> 00:26:53,966
Your face is going to get cakey.

398
00:26:56,466 --> 00:26:58,266
You never learn.

399
00:26:59,000 --> 00:27:00,933
When the sweat flows, the makeup comes off.

400
00:27:05,466 --> 00:27:07,733
Pleng, can I borrow a fan?

401
00:27:07,933 --> 00:27:08,927
No,

402
00:27:09,224 --> 00:27:11,463
Pleng needs it to blow on the computer, it’s hot.

403
00:27:11,700 --> 00:27:16,200
Just give me one, share it, come on!

404
00:27:25,400 --> 00:27:26,462
P’Ploy...

405
00:27:27,205 --> 00:27:28,812
Guy is afraid I can't do it.

406
00:27:29,600 --> 00:27:30,571
You can do it.

407
00:27:31,363 --> 00:27:32,620
The Great Birth Sermon...

408
00:27:32,818 --> 00:27:34,931
You've been performing it
since you were a kid, haven't you?

409
00:27:35,366 --> 00:27:37,533
But Guy has never played Prince Vessantara.

410
00:27:38,066 --> 00:27:40,697
Oh, you've practiced so much.

411
00:27:41,242 --> 00:27:41,742
Listen,

412
00:27:41,742 --> 00:27:42,857
if you can't remember,

413
00:27:42,857 --> 00:27:44,479
just look for P’Phet.

414
00:27:44,479 --> 00:27:45,870
He will help you.

415
00:27:46,068 --> 00:27:47,028
Understand?

416
00:27:48,866 --> 00:27:49,666
Got it.

417
00:27:50,800 --> 00:27:51,622
Pleng,

418
00:27:52,167 --> 00:27:53,966
how is it? Are you used to it yet?

419
00:27:54,266 --> 00:27:56,360
Oh, I’ve got it.

420
00:27:56,657 --> 00:27:58,463
It’s just like when Pleng streams games.

421
00:28:01,733 --> 00:28:02,666
Wait, P’Phet...

422
00:28:03,400 --> 00:28:04,766
What were you thinking...

423
00:28:05,300 --> 00:28:06,366
To do a live stream like this?

424
00:28:07,100 --> 00:28:07,900
Why?

425
00:28:08,800 --> 00:28:09,666
Think about it.

426
00:28:10,133 --> 00:28:11,466
If we live stream like this,

427
00:28:12,066 --> 00:28:14,300
People won't come to see us live.

428
00:28:14,600 --> 00:28:16,800
They’ll just stay home and watch the stream.

429
00:28:18,966 --> 00:28:20,263
You can think of it that way.

430
00:28:20,907 --> 00:28:22,339
But I think differently.

431
00:28:22,933 --> 00:28:26,057
Because I believe the charm of Likay is...

432
00:28:26,057 --> 00:28:28,394
People getting to sit and watch it live
in front of the stage.

433
00:28:28,741 --> 00:28:32,209
As for live streaming,
it's a way to make people know Likay more...

434
00:28:32,209 --> 00:28:33,165
In the social media world.

435
00:28:33,966 --> 00:28:36,519
And it might make the people watching the stream

436
00:28:36,519 --> 00:28:38,100
want to come see it live more too.

437
00:28:42,366 --> 00:28:43,166
Okay.

438
00:28:44,066 --> 00:28:45,566
Whatever you say, I’m in.

439
00:28:45,966 --> 00:28:47,066
Let's do it, little brother.

440
00:28:48,933 --> 00:28:50,000
Brother, look.

441
00:28:50,000 --> 00:28:50,566
Look at this.

442
00:28:50,566 --> 00:28:51,733
Is the picture really this clear?

443
00:28:51,866 --> 00:28:53,700
It's clear. At first, it wasn't very clear.

444
00:28:53,800 --> 00:28:56,166
I went and set it to be clearer.

445
00:29:05,933 --> 00:29:06,589
Oh!

446
00:29:07,134 --> 00:29:08,672
Hello, Headman Mai.

447
00:29:08,919 --> 00:29:10,485
Are you here to see the Petchprakai Troupe too?

448
00:29:11,966 --> 00:29:15,894
No, I just came to check on things.

449
00:29:15,894 --> 00:29:19,066
Because there are many people today,
there might be thieves.

450
00:29:19,300 --> 00:29:20,244
Oh, I see.

451
00:29:20,640 --> 00:29:21,962
I'll excuse myself then.

452
00:29:29,466 --> 00:29:30,266
Father!

453
00:29:30,900 --> 00:29:31,700
Look!

454
00:29:31,966 --> 00:29:33,500
Just a hundred and I got a hand full of snacks.

455
00:29:33,933 --> 00:29:35,133
If it were at Siam,

456
00:29:36,166 --> 00:29:37,700
I probably couldn't even get one egg tart.

457
00:29:37,866 --> 00:29:38,666
Honestly!

458
00:29:38,700 --> 00:29:40,500
And why did you buy so much?

459
00:29:40,766 --> 00:29:42,166
Every time you buy, you never finish it.

460
00:29:43,333 --> 00:29:44,247
By the way,

461
00:29:44,693 --> 00:29:45,817
Where is the Likay stage?

462
00:29:46,666 --> 00:29:49,708
What Likay stage? Today is the Great Birth Sermon.

463
00:29:50,500 --> 00:29:51,800
They’re performing over there at the temple hall.

464
00:29:52,592 --> 00:29:54,545
The Great Birth Sermon?

465
00:29:55,040 --> 00:29:57,028
The one with Chuchok, right?

466
00:29:57,028 --> 00:29:58,244
Yeah, exactly.

467
00:29:59,266 --> 00:30:00,066
Iconic!

468
00:30:00,066 --> 00:30:01,600
Let me clear my memory card for a sec.

469
00:30:02,666 --> 00:30:03,466
Ooh!

470
00:30:03,933 --> 00:30:05,333
Why are you being so extra?

471
00:30:05,766 --> 00:30:08,300
I've brought you to watch Likay
since you were this small.

472
00:30:08,966 --> 00:30:09,766
Ugh.

473
00:30:10,266 --> 00:30:12,300
Just because you went to study in Bangkok,
you act like you don't remember.

474
00:30:12,566 --> 00:30:13,966
I remember that I used to watch it.

475
00:30:14,966 --> 00:30:17,450
But my friends in Bangkok and...

476
00:30:17,450 --> 00:30:19,521
My followers on IG have never seen this.

477
00:30:19,521 --> 00:30:21,381
I'm going to take so many stories.

478
00:30:21,728 --> 00:30:25,100
I’ll help promote the Petchprakai Troupe...

479
00:30:25,348 --> 00:30:26,761
That you're a fan of.

480
00:30:27,800 --> 00:30:29,733
Why are you being so loud, you kid?

481
00:30:29,933 --> 00:30:30,733
Why?

482
00:30:30,933 --> 00:30:31,733
Are you embarrassed?

483
00:30:33,766 --> 00:30:35,166
Embarrassed of what, Daddy?

484
00:30:35,866 --> 00:30:39,000
These days, everyone is a fanboy.

485
00:30:40,166 --> 00:30:40,966
Kaeng Khoi?

486
00:30:41,333 --> 00:30:42,666
Why would you go to Kaeng Khoi?

487
00:30:44,300 --> 00:30:45,966
How can a fanboy be Kaeng Khoi?

488
00:30:48,266 --> 00:30:49,000
Never mind.

489
00:30:49,000 --> 00:30:49,800
I’m not going.

490
00:30:50,266 --> 00:30:51,600
Let's go to the hall.

491
00:30:51,866 --> 00:30:53,566
"Otherwise, we'll get ""Doi"" tickets (faraway seats)."

492
00:30:54,200 --> 00:30:55,933
Is Jom Thian not with this troupe anymore?

493
00:30:56,900 --> 00:30:59,360
Jom Thian hasn't been here for a long time.

494
00:30:59,360 --> 00:31:01,266
He live streams on TikTok, don't you watch him?

495
00:31:01,933 --> 00:31:02,988
Oh!

496
00:31:02,988 --> 00:31:05,771
How would I know?
And what am I supposed to do now? I came from so far.

497
00:31:05,771 --> 00:31:07,466
Oh, what a waste of time.

498
00:31:09,133 --> 00:31:10,133
Hey, young man!

499
00:31:10,733 --> 00:31:11,300
Yes?

500
00:31:11,300 --> 00:31:13,366
You're part of the Petchprakai team, right?

501
00:31:14,266 --> 00:31:15,166
Oh...

502
00:31:15,766 --> 00:31:16,633
Yes, I am.

503
00:31:16,633 --> 00:31:18,200
Go call the troupe leader right now!

504
00:31:18,866 --> 00:31:20,300
You tricked me into coming all this way...

505
00:31:20,400 --> 00:31:21,966
But Father Jom Thian, whom I want to see, isn't here.

506
00:31:22,266 --> 00:31:23,566
How could you do this?

507
00:31:29,000 --> 00:31:29,715
Uh...

508
00:31:30,606 --> 00:31:31,751
Excuse me.

509
00:31:32,593 --> 00:31:33,532
Please be a bit quieter.

510
00:31:33,829 --> 00:31:35,222
The monk is about to start the sermon.

511
00:31:35,519 --> 00:31:36,264
How can I be quiet?

512
00:31:36,759 --> 00:31:38,321
I have to protect my rights!

513
00:31:38,668 --> 00:31:40,483
For being tricked into coming here...

514
00:31:40,483 --> 00:31:43,144
But the Father Jom Thian I want to meet isn't here.

515
00:31:43,266 --> 00:31:44,066
Hmm.

516
00:31:44,933 --> 00:31:47,211
Uh, Mom, please calm down first.

517
00:31:47,211 --> 00:31:50,000
And Mom, do you have glasses? Reading glasses.

518
00:31:50,400 --> 00:31:51,009
Why?

519
00:31:51,009 --> 00:31:51,509
Do you have them?

520
00:31:53,066 --> 00:31:55,966
Oh, right, right. Mom, try putting on your glasses first.

521
00:31:56,900 --> 00:31:57,772
Yes.

522
00:31:57,772 --> 00:32:01,400
And then Mom, try looking this way.
Move a bit, please, move a bit.

523
00:32:02,666 --> 00:32:03,466
Okay, read it again.

524
00:32:03,666 --> 00:32:04,733
One, two, three.

525
00:32:08,933 --> 00:32:10,866
There is no Jom Thian.

526
00:32:13,266 --> 00:32:14,392
"But it’s okay.

527
00:32:14,392 --> 00:32:16,927
Even though your ""Oshi"" has ""Graduated""..."

528
00:32:17,472 --> 00:32:21,283
Since you're already at the temple,
you might as well make some merit.

529
00:32:21,729 --> 00:32:23,769
"Otherwise, it’ll be ""Po"" (exposed)

530
00:32:23,769 --> 00:32:26,198
that you only came to the temple for a man."

531
00:32:27,600 --> 00:32:29,500
Oh, how annoying!

532
00:32:34,100 --> 00:32:35,366
That was funny.

533
00:32:35,666 --> 00:32:37,200
So confused, I heard Jom Thian.

534
00:32:37,466 --> 00:32:38,266
What Jom Thian?

535
00:32:38,400 --> 00:32:39,700
Jom Thian near Pattaya?

536
00:32:39,766 --> 00:32:42,166
Yes, he is with Tho Pra-kai and Ploy Ying.

537
00:32:42,733 --> 00:32:43,533
Uh...

538
00:32:46,200 --> 00:32:47,000
Thanks.

539
00:32:49,366 --> 00:32:52,066
No problem, I got good content.

540
00:32:55,933 --> 00:32:57,133
Are you the cameraman?

541
00:32:59,766 --> 00:33:00,672
Well...

542
00:33:01,514 --> 00:33:02,348
I guess I am.

543
00:33:03,000 --> 00:33:03,886
Great!

544
00:33:04,629 --> 00:33:05,129
Could you...

545
00:33:05,426 --> 00:33:06,285
Help us check this?

546
00:33:06,632 --> 00:33:09,556
We've tried adjusting the camera
following the internet many times...

547
00:33:09,556 --> 00:33:10,782
But no matter how we shoot,

548
00:33:11,672 --> 00:33:14,603
It’s still not clear and not beautiful like others.

549
00:33:15,049 --> 00:33:16,506
You know how to adjust it, right?

550
00:33:16,803 --> 00:33:17,927
Can you help adjust it?

551
00:33:18,866 --> 00:33:20,566
Sure, I can try.

552
00:33:29,400 --> 00:33:30,200
Let’s see.

553
00:33:32,900 --> 00:33:33,700
Wow!

554
00:33:34,166 --> 00:33:35,966
It's as clear as if I shot it with my own eyes.

555
00:33:36,400 --> 00:33:37,266
So cool!

556
00:33:37,700 --> 00:33:38,500
Thank you.

557
00:33:39,533 --> 00:33:40,533
Father!

558
00:33:41,100 --> 00:33:41,933
Three five already!

559
00:33:42,066 --> 00:33:42,733
Oh!

560
00:33:42,733 --> 00:33:44,866
There won't be any seats left. Go, go, go!

561
00:33:48,500 --> 00:33:49,300
Exactly.

562
00:33:53,566 --> 00:33:55,133
I should have asked for her name.

563
00:35:21,266 --> 00:35:22,130
Guy,

564
00:35:22,477 --> 00:35:24,547
You played really well today.

565
00:35:24,900 --> 00:35:25,700
Mm-hmm.

566
00:35:26,000 --> 00:35:27,367
Drink some warm water.

567
00:35:27,912 --> 00:35:29,278
It will help save your voice.

568
00:35:30,533 --> 00:35:31,333
Heh.

569
00:35:31,466 --> 00:35:34,300
With your own brother,
you'd never do something like this.

570
00:35:36,466 --> 00:35:37,966
Don't you have legs?

571
00:35:38,300 --> 00:35:39,666
Always complaining with that mouth of yours.

572
00:35:39,966 --> 00:35:41,166
The flask is right there.

573
00:35:41,700 --> 00:35:42,766
So biased!

574
00:35:47,300 --> 00:35:48,100
Hey!

575
00:35:48,933 --> 00:35:50,166
I have to go now.

576
00:35:50,533 --> 00:35:52,900
P’Phet asked me to go thank the host.

577
00:36:16,933 --> 00:36:17,766
What are you looking at?

578
00:36:19,866 --> 00:36:20,666
Not telling.

579
00:36:24,166 --> 00:36:25,400
Something’s fishy.

580
00:36:26,600 --> 00:36:29,266
To the point where you have
to set an alarm to watch...

581
00:36:29,866 --> 00:36:30,606
What is it?

582
00:36:30,606 --> 00:36:31,106
Oh!

583
00:36:32,333 --> 00:36:34,200
When you stream games all day, I don't bother you.

584
00:36:34,333 --> 00:36:35,900
If you don't want to mind my business,
then it’s my business!

585
00:36:36,266 --> 00:36:37,400
Well, I want to mind your business!

586
00:36:38,733 --> 00:36:39,533
Ugh.

587
00:36:43,200 --> 00:36:44,266
I want to be you.

588
00:36:46,100 --> 00:36:48,600
What? Why do you suddenly want to be me?

589
00:36:49,366 --> 00:36:52,686
Just being stupid and chill.

590
00:36:52,934 --> 00:36:55,579
Doing whatever you want,
and not doing what you don't want to do.

591
00:36:59,666 --> 00:37:01,000
Are you insulting me?

592
00:37:01,866 --> 00:37:02,666
Huh?

593
00:37:02,866 --> 00:37:04,066
How is being you not good?

594
00:37:04,366 --> 00:37:07,533
Living comfortably,
with someone taking care of everything.

595
00:37:08,166 --> 00:37:09,400
You should try being me then.

596
00:37:10,066 --> 00:37:10,933
Then you’ll know.

597
00:37:19,966 --> 00:37:21,333
But you can't be me.

598
00:37:25,300 --> 00:37:26,400
Because you aren't handsome.

599
00:37:27,966 --> 00:37:29,966
I'm going to help Ping Pong Chae pack up.

600
00:37:32,500 --> 00:37:33,400
Insulting me just like that.

601
00:37:34,800 --> 00:37:35,600
Hmph.

602
00:37:38,566 --> 00:37:40,366
You stay here alone, watch your back.

603
00:37:42,900 --> 00:37:44,466
I heard that around here...

604
00:37:47,066 --> 00:37:48,566
It used to be an old cemetery.

605
00:37:53,133 --> 00:37:53,933
Guy!

606
00:37:54,566 --> 00:37:55,700
Wait for me for a sec!

607
00:37:57,766 --> 00:37:58,566
Guy!

608
00:38:00,166 --> 00:38:01,903
The performance fee, I already transferred it.

609
00:38:02,299 --> 00:38:05,330
But this is a special bonus,
please give it to the others too.

610
00:38:05,578 --> 00:38:07,698
Today you guys's show was very entertaining.

611
00:38:08,166 --> 00:38:08,985
Thank you.

612
00:38:09,530 --> 00:38:10,030
May you be prosperous and wealthy.

613
00:38:10,872 --> 00:38:11,372
I’ll take my leave now.

614
00:38:11,401 --> 00:38:12,501
Yes, sir. Goodbye.

615
00:38:17,100 --> 00:38:17,900
Oops!

616
00:38:18,466 --> 00:38:19,266
What!?

617
00:38:20,500 --> 00:38:21,466
Quite a lot, huh?

618
00:38:22,300 --> 00:38:23,499
So, P’Phet...

619
00:38:24,539 --> 00:38:25,462
This month,

620
00:38:25,462 --> 00:38:27,351
We have enough money to pay Mr. Ar, right?

621
00:38:29,800 --> 00:38:31,533
This is for this month.

622
00:38:32,966 --> 00:38:34,800
As for next month, we have to keep fighting.

623
00:38:36,000 --> 00:38:37,531
Always fighting.

624
00:38:38,274 --> 00:38:38,774
Today,

625
00:38:39,269 --> 00:38:40,972
Pleng came to tell me too...

626
00:38:41,220 --> 00:38:44,038
That our live stream had a hundred viewers!

627
00:38:44,979 --> 00:38:45,687
I think

628
00:38:45,687 --> 00:38:48,166
we can definitely attract some new fans.

629
00:38:51,133 --> 00:38:52,622
And then...

630
00:38:52,870 --> 00:38:55,665
I will try calling the old hosts.

631
00:38:56,408 --> 00:38:59,313
In case someone still has mercy for us.

632
00:39:02,666 --> 00:39:03,869
P’Phet, you should...

633
00:39:05,206 --> 00:39:06,464
Get some rest too.

634
00:39:07,733 --> 00:39:08,691
I...

635
00:39:09,088 --> 00:39:11,566
Secretly saw your light on until late every night.

636
00:39:14,566 --> 00:39:15,615
I also…

637
00:39:16,457 --> 00:39:17,266
can't sleep well.

638
00:39:19,400 --> 00:39:20,927
I'm worried about everything.

639
00:39:23,007 --> 00:39:24,249
Once Father was gone...

640
00:39:26,031 --> 00:39:27,099
It made me realize that

641
00:39:27,099 --> 00:39:29,455
carrying the Petchprakai Troupe alone...

642
00:39:30,841 --> 00:39:31,854
Is truly very difficult.

643
00:39:35,468 --> 00:39:36,864
"What do you mean ""alone,"" Brother?"

644
00:39:38,700 --> 00:39:39,808
Didn't you see, Ploy?

645
00:39:41,293 --> 00:39:42,387
That once Father was gone,

646
00:39:43,427 --> 00:39:45,560
Once Jom Thian was gone, once Chan Dao was gone,

647
00:39:46,402 --> 00:39:47,995
Hosts contact us for work less often.

648
00:39:50,000 --> 00:39:52,904
And the seats are empty.

649
00:39:53,820 --> 00:39:56,416
When I see the empty chairs,

650
00:39:56,416 --> 00:39:57,880
it makes me realize it used to be easy...

651
00:39:58,276 --> 00:39:59,362
Because everyone was there.

652
00:40:00,866 --> 00:40:03,100
But now that it’s just me,

653
00:40:05,333 --> 00:40:06,133
It's...

654
00:40:09,666 --> 00:40:10,466
And what about me?

655
00:40:13,766 --> 00:40:14,566
Guy?

656
00:40:15,133 --> 00:40:15,933
Pleng?

657
00:40:16,533 --> 00:40:17,866
Ping Pong Chae?

658
00:40:19,733 --> 00:40:21,466
Do we have no meaning to you at all?

659
00:40:24,100 --> 00:40:25,600
I’ve always told you,

660
00:40:26,000 --> 00:40:27,400
That you still have us.

661
00:40:28,366 --> 00:40:30,800
Why do you always say you're all alone?

662
00:40:31,933 --> 00:40:34,066
Have you ever seen us in your eyes?

663
00:40:35,300 --> 00:40:36,600
Guy, your brother...

664
00:40:36,966 --> 00:40:38,800
He recites poetry all day and all night.

665
00:40:39,666 --> 00:40:41,733
As for Pleng, he’s learning to use the OB switcher.

666
00:40:42,266 --> 00:40:44,733
Ping Pong Chae has become more responsible.

667
00:40:47,066 --> 00:40:48,667
All of our efforts...

668
00:40:49,558 --> 00:40:51,447
Have no value in your eyes?

669
00:40:53,500 --> 00:40:55,211
It's not like that, Ploy. It’s...

670
00:40:56,251 --> 00:40:56,966
I’m just stressed.

671
00:40:57,166 --> 00:40:58,621
I already told you,

672
00:41:00,000 --> 00:41:01,260
That if you need me,

673
00:41:02,844 --> 00:41:03,857
I will stay with you.

674
00:41:07,800 --> 00:41:09,566
But if you don't need me anymore...

675
00:41:11,800 --> 00:41:12,866
I can leave.

676
00:41:17,094 --> 00:41:18,000
Ploy!

677
00:41:49,500 --> 00:41:50,700
Guy, wait for me!

678
00:41:54,500 --> 00:41:55,566
Where did he go?

679
00:42:19,933 --> 00:42:20,800
Ghosts aren't real.

680
00:42:48,466 --> 00:42:49,700
You're taking advantage of me!

681
00:42:51,000 --> 00:42:52,038
No, no, I...

682
00:42:52,830 --> 00:42:54,243
Didn't mean to do that, I...

683
00:42:54,986 --> 00:42:56,246
You teased me.

684
00:42:57,236 --> 00:42:59,763
I just teased you back for content.

685
00:43:05,066 --> 00:43:07,500
And why are you standing in the dark like this?

686
00:43:08,100 --> 00:43:08,967
Waiting for Father.

687
00:43:09,513 --> 00:43:10,200
He’s probably here.

688
00:43:10,200 --> 00:43:10,700
Gone.

689
00:43:10,900 --> 00:43:11,766
Hey, wait a sec!

690
00:43:14,133 --> 00:43:14,933
Well...

691
00:43:16,766 --> 00:43:18,600
Just now, I hadn't asked for your name yet.

692
00:43:20,400 --> 00:43:21,333
What’s your name?

693
00:43:22,366 --> 00:43:22,866
Can I...

694
00:43:23,163 --> 00:43:24,200
Get your contact?

695
00:43:27,133 --> 00:43:27,933
Are you hitting on me?

696
00:43:29,366 --> 00:43:30,166
Well...

697
00:43:32,666 --> 00:43:34,000
If it’s to be friends...

698
00:43:35,166 --> 00:43:36,333
My friend list is full.

699
00:43:37,100 --> 00:43:37,628
But...

700
00:43:38,272 --> 00:43:39,449
If it’s to be a boyfriend...

701
00:43:39,966 --> 00:43:41,866
You’ll have to fight a bit.

702
00:43:42,133 --> 00:43:44,866
"Because I’m ""Hard Mode."""

703
00:43:46,000 --> 00:43:47,566
Ooh, Daddy is here.

704
00:43:52,400 --> 00:43:53,466
Hard Mode?

705
00:43:54,400 --> 00:43:57,400
I’ve finished many games on Hard Mode.

706
00:44:06,400 --> 00:44:07,900
Don't go yet, wait!

707
00:44:46,133 --> 00:44:47,238
How was it?

708
00:44:48,080 --> 00:44:48,877
Exhausting, right?

709
00:44:50,000 --> 00:44:51,250
I told you when you dance,

710
00:44:51,250 --> 00:44:52,522
you must mind the beat, understand?

711
00:44:52,918 --> 00:44:54,308
Tilt left, tilt right.

712
00:44:54,952 --> 00:44:56,213
Just like I showed you.

713
00:44:56,609 --> 00:44:57,241
Just...

714
00:44:58,182 --> 00:44:59,802
Remember and use it.

715
00:45:01,335 --> 00:45:03,233
Today, thank you everyone very much for...

716
00:45:03,827 --> 00:45:04,942
Being dedicated to the rehearsal.

717
00:45:05,586 --> 00:45:07,920
And don't forget to take what I taught...

718
00:45:08,910 --> 00:45:10,099
To adjust and use as well.

719
00:45:10,347 --> 00:45:11,773
Regarding the dancing and...

720
00:45:11,773 --> 00:45:13,035
The rhythms and things like that too.

721
00:45:13,876 --> 00:45:16,708
As for this Saturday and Sunday,
I want you to rest fully.

722
00:45:17,748 --> 00:45:18,447
Because...

723
00:45:19,190 --> 00:45:19,919
Next week...

724
00:45:20,513 --> 00:45:22,430
Work might be coming in.

725
00:45:23,568 --> 00:45:24,615
Work?

726
00:45:24,615 --> 00:45:25,773
There’s work!

727
00:45:25,773 --> 00:45:26,620
Work!

728
00:45:30,000 --> 00:45:30,820
There’s work, guys!

729
00:45:31,750 --> 00:45:32,498
What’s wrong?

730
00:45:32,533 --> 00:45:33,333
What’s wrong with you?

731
00:45:35,733 --> 00:45:37,566
Okay, kids, go rest.

732
00:45:38,366 --> 00:45:39,533
Let's go rest.

733
00:45:40,800 --> 00:45:42,400
Going to rest now.

734
00:45:45,300 --> 00:45:46,100
Walk carefully.

735
00:46:04,102 --> 00:46:04,968
What are you two sulking about?

736
00:46:08,300 --> 00:46:10,100
Can you tell?

737
00:46:10,933 --> 00:46:12,068
It would be bad if I couldn't.

738
00:46:12,466 --> 00:46:14,100
Your faces have been sour for two days.

739
00:46:24,200 --> 00:46:25,166
Go eat.

740
00:46:41,500 --> 00:46:42,933
Isn't it suffocating being like this?

741
00:46:48,133 --> 00:46:48,933
I’m sorry.

742
00:46:51,400 --> 00:46:52,733
Can we talk?

743
00:46:56,566 --> 00:46:57,400
Talk about what?

744
00:46:58,533 --> 00:47:01,933
Talk about anything you want to say, Ploy.

745
00:47:03,266 --> 00:47:04,600
You can scold me.

746
00:47:06,766 --> 00:47:07,566
You said it yourself.

747
00:47:09,900 --> 00:47:10,827
I can scold you.

748
00:47:12,015 --> 00:47:13,249
But keep it light.

749
00:47:14,437 --> 00:47:15,514
My heart is fragile.

750
00:47:25,466 --> 00:47:26,616
P’Phet, do you know…

751
00:47:28,249 --> 00:47:30,000
everyone must have felt lonely at some point?

752
00:47:37,000 --> 00:47:38,200
Can I sit with you?

753
00:47:42,366 --> 00:47:43,900
When Mom and Dad died...

754
00:47:45,366 --> 00:47:47,766
Pleng was so addicted to games he
wouldn't come home.

755
00:47:49,100 --> 00:47:50,966
At that time, I was so anxious.

756
00:47:53,466 --> 00:47:55,200
Why is the world so cruel?

757
00:47:58,766 --> 00:48:00,766
To leave me feeling so lonely like this.

758
00:48:13,733 --> 00:48:15,800
But P’Phet Thae came to help me.

759
00:48:19,800 --> 00:48:21,366
Can I join you for a meal?

760
00:48:22,885 --> 00:48:23,685
Yes.

761
00:48:43,342 --> 00:48:44,525
♪ Full moon night… ♪

762
00:48:44,525 --> 00:48:45,720
♪ Looking out...♪

763
00:48:45,720 --> 00:48:47,573
♪ Pleasant to the eyes...♪

764
00:48:48,464 --> 00:48:50,583
♪ In the middle of the moon...♪

765
00:48:50,583 --> 00:48:53,156
♪ The old folks said...♪

766
00:48:55,434 --> 00:48:58,486
♪The grandma and grandpa were farming,
just the two of them.♪

767
00:49:01,466 --> 00:49:03,666
I just want to repay you some way.

768
00:49:05,966 --> 00:49:08,000
I want to be the one who stays by your side.

769
00:49:09,800 --> 00:49:10,866
I want to be the person that when you...

770
00:49:12,566 --> 00:49:14,333
Turn back anytime, you will find me.

771
00:49:25,383 --> 00:49:26,214
Ploy, do you know?

772
00:49:27,551 --> 00:49:28,576
For me...

773
00:49:30,236 --> 00:49:31,892
You aren't just a younger sister.

774
00:49:37,733 --> 00:49:38,654
But...

775
00:49:39,298 --> 00:49:40,910
You are like...

776
00:49:48,666 --> 00:49:50,400
Another best friend of mine.

777
00:49:53,166 --> 00:49:54,100
Thank you very much.

778
00:49:56,000 --> 00:49:56,800
Hmm.

779
00:49:58,166 --> 00:49:59,266
Best friends, huh?

780
00:50:06,066 --> 00:50:07,133
Are you still mad?

781
00:51:26,202 --> 00:51:28,420
I am a poor Likay actor...

782
00:51:28,420 --> 00:51:30,158
Living on the Thonburi side, Tha Phra...

783
00:51:30,672 --> 00:51:32,424
I am a Likay actor, yes...

784
00:51:32,424 --> 00:51:34,261
Living on the Thonburi side, Tha Phra...

785
00:51:35,400 --> 00:51:36,933
No, the second verse goes like this, listen to me.

786
00:51:36,933 --> 00:51:37,733
You guys listen to me.

787
00:51:38,366 --> 00:51:40,533
Ah, ah, I am a poor Likay actor...

788
00:51:40,966 --> 00:51:42,366
Living on the Thonburi side, Tha Phra...

789
00:51:42,933 --> 00:51:44,300
I am a Tha Phra Likay actor...

790
00:51:44,933 --> 00:51:46,466
"Living in the Thonburi side na ja..."

791
00:51:47,500 --> 00:51:48,000
Wait.

792
00:51:48,000 --> 00:51:48,500
Is that right?

793
00:51:48,866 --> 00:51:49,366
Yes.

794
00:51:49,366 --> 00:51:49,866
No.

795
00:51:50,333 --> 00:51:50,900
Is it like that?

796
00:51:50,900 --> 00:51:51,533
Yes.

797
00:51:51,533 --> 00:51:52,762
Like mine, like mine.

798
00:51:52,762 --> 00:51:53,666
Like mine, it's correct.

799
00:51:53,966 --> 00:51:55,133
I am a poor man Likay...

800
00:51:55,133 --> 00:51:55,825
This guy is making things up.

801
00:51:56,366 --> 00:51:58,000
No, he’s really making it up now.

802
00:51:58,300 --> 00:51:59,100
Have you seen Guy?

803
00:51:59,366 --> 00:52:00,312
(Ping) Seen him.
(Pong) Haven't seen him.(Chae) Seen him.

804
00:52:02,500 --> 00:52:03,566
So have you seen him or not?

805
00:52:03,766 --> 00:52:04,645
(Ping) Seen him. (Pong) Seen him.
(Chae) Haven't seen him.

806
00:52:05,800 --> 00:52:06,966
Do you two even see anything?

807
00:52:07,533 --> 00:52:08,333
Seen it.

808
00:52:14,118 --> 00:52:16,314
Should be around here.

809
00:52:17,453 --> 00:52:19,621
Then there will be someone saying...

810
00:52:19,621 --> 00:52:20,321
Ah, thank you very much.

811
00:52:20,321 --> 00:52:20,821
Yes.

812
00:52:20,821 --> 00:52:22,016
Thank you very much, then get startled.

813
00:52:48,357 --> 00:52:50,057
♪ Even if… ♪

814
00:52:50,404 --> 00:52:52,754
♪ The body is tired...♪

815
00:52:53,066 --> 00:52:55,512
♪ The heart is tired...♪

816
00:52:56,947 --> 00:53:00,200
♪ We won't give up...♪

817
00:53:00,646 --> 00:53:02,190
♪ Won't waver.♪

818
00:53:03,328 --> 00:53:05,887
♪ Hundreds of problems...♪

819
00:53:06,284 --> 00:53:08,970
♪ That come our way...♪

820
00:53:10,000 --> 00:53:14,978
♪ I won't be afraid of anything.♪

821
00:53:15,572 --> 00:53:17,779
♪ Every problem...♪

822
00:53:18,472 --> 00:53:21,078
♪ I will overcome...♪

823
00:53:22,019 --> 00:53:25,632
♪ For my dream...♪

824
00:53:26,573 --> 00:53:30,752
♪ To come true.♪

825
00:53:33,666 --> 00:53:35,200
Are you interested in being an actor?

826
00:53:35,400 --> 00:53:36,556
Huh?

827
00:53:36,556 --> 00:53:37,466
You're so cute in person.

828
00:53:37,766 --> 00:53:40,333
But soon, our troupe will have someone on TV!

829
00:53:40,500 --> 00:53:42,300
Next week, no one needs to go on TV yet.

830
